            "value": "%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20Sea%20of%20Galilee%2C%20Satan%20was%20holding%20a%20choice%20prisoner.%20This%20man%2C%20totally%20bound%20by%20Satan%2C%20was%20naked%20and%20homeless.%20When%20Jesus%20arrived%20on%20the%20scene%2C%20the%20demons%20in%20the%20man%20violently%20protested.%20We%20need%20not%20think%20that%20we%20will%20invade%20darkened%20lands%2C%20cultures%2C%20and%20strongholds%20without%20experiencing%20resistance.%20Someone%20said%2C%20%22If%20you%20never%20run%20into%20the%20devil%2C%20you%20must%20be%20going%20the%20same%20way!%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESatan%20hates%20our%20mission.%20We%20are%20traveling%20into%20his%20territory%2C%20invading%20the%20kingdom%20of%20darkness.%20The%20storms%20we%20encounter%20are%20diversions%20to%20discourage%20us%20from%20reaching%20those%20whom%20Satan%20considers%20his%20trophies.%20When%20Jesus%20set%20out%20to%20confront%20the%20demoniac%2C%20Satan%20tried%20to%20stop%20him.%20A%20storm%20%22came%20down%22%20(v.%2023%20NIV)%2C%20but%20Jesus%20%22got%20up%22%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
